<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-10-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Persistent Human Cosavirus Infection in Lung Transplant Recipient, Italy</TITLE><BODY>Human cosavirus is a novel picornavirus recently identified in feces from children in southern Asia. We report infection with human cosavirus in a patient in the Mediterranean area. The patient was an adult double lung transplant recipient who had chronic diarrhea associated with persistent infection with human cosavirus.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>